record_data.record_narrative_name: UGI Development Company, Electric Tariff No. 3, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service from the Hunlock Creek Power Station located in Hunlock Creek, Pennsylvania
record_data.record_plain_text: UGI DEVELOPMENT COMPANY Electric Tariff No. 3 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service UGI Development Company ("UGID") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power") from the Hunlock Creek Power Station located in Hunlock Creek, Pennsylvania, to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This Rate Schedule FERC No. 2, sets for UGID's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power, as contemplated by the revised Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Power. UGID's monthly revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the following: (1) Fixed Capability Component; and (2) Heating Losses Component. Total charges for any 12-month period will not be less than the sum of the annual charges specified below. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: 1) FIXED CAPABILITY COMPONENT The annual revenue requirement for the Fixed Capability Component is $769,587.35. The monthly charge to PJM is $64,132.28. 2) HEATING LOSSES COMPONENT The annual revenue requirement for the Heating Losses Component is $437,172.88. The monthly charge to PJM is $36,431.07. The total Reactive Power Annual Revenue Requirement is $1,206,760.23. The total monthly charge to PJM is $100,563.35.

record_data.record_plain_text: UGI DEVELOPMENT COMPANY FERC ELECTRIC RATE SCHEDULE NO. 1 1. Availability: UGI Development Company ("UGI Development" or "Seller") makes electric energy and capacity available for sale for resale under this Rate Schedule to any purchaser, including to any affiliate that does not have captive customers. 2. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Northeast Region and a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), in the Southeast, Northwest, Central, Southwest, and Southwest Power Pool Regions. 3. Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by UGI Development not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of UGI Development. 4. Rates: All sales of electric energy and capacity shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and UGI Development. 5. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and UGI Development. 6. Ancillary Services: RTO/ISO Specific PJM: UGI Development offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. New York: UGI Development offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. New England: UGI Development offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. California: UGI Development offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. Midcontinent ISO: UGI Development offers regulation service, operating reserve service (which includes a 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("Midcontinent ISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the Midcontinent ISO. Third Party Provider Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 7. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff. 8. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Pursuant to Commission order in Docket No. ER98-2817-000 (July 1, 1999), UGI Development has received: a. a waiver of accounting and other requirements of Parts 41, 101, and 141 of the Commission's regulations; b. waiver of the filing requirements of the provisions of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's Regulations, with the exception of sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 36.16; and c. blanket authorization for issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. 824c and Part 34 of the Commission's Regulations; provided that the Commission reserves the right to require a further showing that neither the public nor private interests will be adversely affected by continued Commission approval of issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities. 9. Effective Date: This Tariff is effective on the date authorized by the Commission.
